<h2><%- include('github-link', {
  href: '/src/ejs/sideways-scrolling.ejs',
  content: 'Sideways Scrolling with Mouse&nbsp;Wheel',
}); %></h2>

<p>Users may prefer to scroll sideways by using the mouse&nbsp;wheel normally, especially when the scrollbar is not&nbsp;visible. To&nbsp;enable this behaviour, set&nbsp;<code>captureWheel: true</code> in the&nbsp;options. This will translate mouse&nbsp;wheel movement to horizontal&nbsp;scrolling.</p>

<div class='example-container'>
  <div id='mousewheel'>
    <p class='horizontal-text'>Horizontal Fade Scroller</p>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  new FadeScroll.Horizontal('#mousewheel', {
    hideScrollbar: true,
    captureWheel: true,
  }).mount();
</script>